property.definition: Connects a Thing to a Thing that follows or followed it in some sequence.
property.scope_note: The relation does not specify by itself what criteria are used for ordering the sequence. There may actually be zero to many intermediate Entities, ignored or unkown, in the sequence between the two connected Things. Can be used, for example, for specifying that some Record 'precedes' (has next) some Record within a Record Set.
property.NEW_CHANGE_NOTE: changed the IRI, label, inverse property IRI, text definition, corresponding CM component name.
